Connect TO Permira, connect To growth

Permira is a global investment firm that finds and backs successful businesses with ambition. We share our deep sector insight and network of senior specialists to help our partners grow their businesses into worldwide industry leaders.



Hear from our Co-Managing Partners
                                    









Investment conviction in uncertain markets

Permira thrives on complexity. Our sector teams look ‘beyond the macro’ to identify pockets of sustainable growth, as was the case with Hugo Boss. Hear more about the Permira approach from our Co-Managing Partners Tom Lister and Kurt Björklund.



Click to watch our video
                                    









Sushiro

Akindo Sushiro is a market-leading ‘Kaiten’ sushi restaurant chain operator in Japan that listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange in March 2017. Hear from Ryo Fujii, Head of Japan, and Sushiro’s Koichi Mizutome, President & CEO, and Steve Dacus, Chairman, on how menu diversification, technology and expansion has played a major part in the company’s growth.



Click to watch our video
                                    









Intelligrated

Intelligrated has undergone a period of tremendous growth, which included increasing its revenue by more than 90% and winning several major new customers which has helped drive a 300% growth in the Company’s sales pipeline. Hear more from Intelligrated’s CEO, Chris Cole, and President and COO, Jim McCarthy, along with Richard Carey, Partner and Co-Head of Industrials at Permira.



Click to watch our video
                                    









2016 Highlights

2016 was a successful year for us. We welcomed seven new businesses to the portfolio and saw some significant realisations across our funds. We launched and closed our latest fund, Permira VI, at €7.5 billion.
Permira Debt Managers also continued to grow strongly and will be celebrating its 10th anniversary this year.
 



Watch our highlights from the year
                                    









Informatica

Anil Chakravarthy, CEO of Informatica, and Brian Ruder, Permira’s Co-Head of Technology, shows how Informatica’s clients are using data management systems to get a single view of the customer and then using that to create real business value.



Click to watch our video
                                    














