Permira IV, L.P.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 5:25 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Permira IV, L.P.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Permira IV, L.P. specializes in buyouts, buyins, late venture, emerging growth, and growth capital investments. It invests in consumers, chemicals, industrial products and services, technology, media, healthcare, financial services, online services, wireless networking equipments, internet and direct marketing retail, mobile data services, and telecom sector. The fund seeks to invest globally and at least 70 percent of the capital in Europe. It may invest up to 30 percent of its committed capital in businesses which do not have or intend to have significant activities in Europe. It also invests in Asia and United States. The fund can invest in takeovers worth up to £3.5 billion ($6.46 billio...
Permira IV, L.P. specializes in buyouts, buyins, late venture, emerging growth, and growth capital investments. It invests in consumers, chemicals, industrial products and services, technology, media, healthcare, financial services, online services, wireless networking equipments, internet and direct marketing retail, mobile data services, and telecom sector. The fund seeks to invest globally and at least 70 percent of the capital in Europe. It may invest up to 30 percent of its committed capital in businesses which do not have or intend to have significant activities in Europe. It also invests in Asia and United States. The fund can invest in takeovers worth up to £3.5 billion ($6.46 billion). It seeks to invest between €150 million ($215 million) and €500 million ($716.68 million) per transaction. The investment could sometimes be slightly smaller or larger than these amounts but this is the general rule. The fund prefers to hold a large equity stake in its portfolio companies. It prefers taking minority public equity stakes or hold a listed company's shares ahead of making a takeover effect. The fund consists of P4 Co-Investment LP, Permira IV Continuing LP 1 and Permira IV Continuing LP 2.
Detailed Description


80 Pall MallLondon,  SW1Y 5ESUnited KingdomFounded in 2006



Phone: 44 20 7632 1000

Fax: 44 20 7930 3185








